    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_7_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "Offered for the serious driver is this 2011 Porsche Cayman S, a definitive example of the 987.2 platform. At its heart lies a 3.4L flat-six featuring Direct Fuel Injection (DFI), delivering a linear power band and eliminating the IMS bearing concerns of earlier iterations. The mid-engine configuration provides a low polar moment of inertia, resulting in exceptional rotational balance through high-speed transitions. This specimen is equipped with the 7-speed PDK dual-clutch transmission, offering rapid-fire gear changes and optimized shift points via integrated hydraulic actuators. The suspension retains its factory-spec geometry, utilizing MacPherson struts to provide communicative feedback through the hydraulic power steering rack. Braking performance is maintained by four-piston aluminum monobloc fixed calipers clamping onto cross-drilled rotors for superior heat dissipation. While exhibiting minor cosmetic road wear consistent with its mileage, the drivetrain remains robust with documented service intervals, ensuring the mechanical integrity required for spirited technical driving.",
